lines.text: da dadab dada dadab da-a
da dadab dada dadab da-a
stars shining bright above you
night breezes seem to whisper "i love you"
birds singing in the sycamore tree
dream a little dream of me
say ninety-nine and kiss me
just hold me tight
and tell me you'll miss me
while i'm as blue, as blue as can be
dream a little dream of me-e
stars fading, but i linger on, dear
still craving your kiss
i'm longing to linger till dawn, dear
just saying this:
sweet dreams till sun beams find you
sweet dreams that leave
our worries behind you
but in your dreams, whatever they'll be
dream a little dream of me-e
